    %h2
      %a{ href: "/interviews/david_varela"}David Varela

    David is a writer and producer working in a huge range of media, including theatre, radio, film, games and interactive drama. He started writing live online in 2012, when he spent 100 hours taking commissions in Ted Hughes’ old house for a fundraising project called 100 Hours of Solitude. The tech for that project – developed by Riccardo Cambiassi and Alex Heeton – now forms the basis of the Live Writing Series site. www.davidvarela.com

