    %h2.media-heading Gemma Seltzer

    Gemma is a writer working online, live and in print. Her digital writing projects include The View from Here, original stories produced live; 5am London, a fictional blog; and Look up at the Sky, which charted the peaceful parts of the city through walking and writing. Gemma is the author of blog-to-book Speak to Strangers, 100 stories of a hundred words about random conversations with Londoners (Penned in the Margins, 2011). She has presented her work on BBC radio, at Latitude festival and the Venice Biennale. Gemma was writer in residence for the Olympic torch relay in Devon. www.gemmaseltzer.co.uk

